        <abstract>
            <p>Had it not been for CD, JDH would never have written such papers as his one on Arctic flora. The "evulgation" of CD’s views is the purest pleasure he derives from them.</p> 
<p>He too is staggered that Greenland ought to have been depopulated during the glacial period. Absence of <hi rend="italic">Caltha</hi> is fatal to its re-population by chance migration.</p> 
        </abstract>
